    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-05-31T09:17:55+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-31T09:17:55+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-30T23:47:55Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-30T23:47:55Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A weak high pressure system moves across from the west today. A significant low pressure system moves over waters to the south of SA on Monday and Tuesday reaching western Bass Strait Tuesday afternoon. A another low pressure moves over waters to the southeast on Wednesday. A high pressure system follows the low moving across northern parts of SA later in the week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW010" description="West Coast" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-05-31T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-01T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-30T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-31T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. High chance of showers, most likely in the late afternoon and evening. Winds northerly 25 to 35 km/h. Daytime maximum temperatures between 17 and 23.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 11:10am to 1:50pm, UV Index predicted to reach 3 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-06-01T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-02T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-31T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-01T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Very high chance of showers south of Streaky Bay, medium chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm. Damaging winds possible. Winds northerly 25 to 35 km/h turning west to northwesterly 40 to 60 km/h during the morning and early afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 12 and 15 with daytime temperatures reaching the low 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-06-02T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-03T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-01T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-02T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Very high chance of showers east of Ceduna, medium chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm south of Streaky Bay in the morning. Winds westerly 30 to 45 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 10 and 13 with daytime temperatures reaching around 19.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-06-03T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-04T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-02T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-03T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Very high chance of showers east of Ceduna, medium chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm south of Streaky Bay in the evening. Winds west to northwesterly 25 to 35 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to around 9 with daytime temperatures reaching between 17 and 20.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
